external_knowledge:
- "blossoming treasures" refers to the products;
- "in the vault of knowledge" is a metaphor for the inventory system;
- "sprouted in the fertile ground of size 10" means the products have size_id = 10;
- "nestled within the walls of the third stronghold" refers to the products being in warehouse_id = 3;
- "have not yet been plucked from their shelves" denotes the condition of having a quantity greater than 0.

sql:
SELECT stores.store_name, AVG(sales.quantity) AS average_quantity
FROM sales
INNER JOIN stores ON sales.store_id = stores.store_id
WHERE sales.sale_date IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT sale_date FROM sales WHERE store_id IN (
        SELECT store_id FROM stores WHERE store_name LIKE '%Grocery%'
    )
)
AND sales.quantity > (
    SELECT MIN(quantity) FROM sales WHERE store_id IN (
        SELECT store_id FROM stores WHERE store_name LIKE '%Grocery%'
    )
)
GROUP BY stores.store_name
HAVING average_quantity > (SELECT AVG(quantity) FROM sales);

SELECT color, AVG(CAST(weight AS FLOAT)) AS average_weight
FROM products
GROUP BY color;
